    "original_title": "Brooklyn: Ralph Avenue - Broadway",
    "text": "Ralph Ave. (man thereon), at the southwest corner of Broadway (elevated structure thereon) showing a three-story frame structure known as Cobly Hall in 1875. Church services were held here from 1875-1877 by the Trinity Baptist Church, and in 1884, by the German Presbyterian Friedess Kirche. It was subsequently known as Ridgewood Hall; Schumacher's Cafe once occupied the ground floor.\n\nJune 1923\n\nEugene L. Armbruster Collection.\n",
